burnToReedem(uint256,uint256).details: Burns a token to reedem a physical piece of the art

params._givenCode: The code given to the token
params._tokenId: The ID of the token to burn

params._baseUri: The base URI of the contract
params._minterContractAddress: The address of the minter contract
params.initialOwner: The initial owner of the contract

getAllTokensVersion().details: Returns an array of versions for all tokens

returns.versions: An array of versions for all tokens

getTokenVersion(uint256).details: Returns the version of a specific token

mint(address,uint256).details: Mints a new token and assigns it to the specified recipient

params.recipient: The address to receive the minted token

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

refreshToken(uint256).details: Refreshes the version of a specific token

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBaseURI(string).details: Sets the base URI for token URIsOnly the owner can call this function

setFundsReceiverAddress(address).details: Sets the address of the funds receiverOnly the owner can call this function

params.newFundsReceiverAddress: The address of the funds receiver

setMinterContractAddress(address).details: Sets the address of the minter contractOnly the owner can call this function

params.newMinterContractAddress: The address of the minter contract

setRefreshTokenPrice(uint256).details: Sets the price of the refresh tokenOnly the owner can call this function

params.newRefreshTokenPriceInWei: The new price of the refresh token

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Checks if a specific interface is supported by the contract

returns._0: True if the interface is supported, false otherwise

tokenURI(uint256).details: Returns the URI of a specific token

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers a token from one address to another

params.from: The address to transfer the token from
params.to: The address to transfer the token to
params.tokenId: The ID of the token to transfer

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
